evidence_span: The controlling factor for nodular corrosion behavior is related to the matrix concentration of Fe, Cr, and Ni in Zircaloy. The depletion of solute elements is the cause of poor nodular corrosion resistance. Cold work also has a definite effect on the nodular corrosion resistance of the material, which is probably due to the yield stress of the substrate.
